What the white ONE OWNER, ACCIDENT FREE 2018 Jeep Grand Cherokee Overland was to its previous owner, has been hinted; what, at times, he was to me, as yet remains unsaid. Aside from those more obvious considerations touching Grand Cherokee, like the heated and cooled leather seats, power liftgate, remote start, and more, which could not but occasionally awaken in any man's soul some alarm, there was another thought, or rather vague, nameless horror concerning him. It was the whiteness of the Jeep that above all things appalled me. Though in many natural objects, whiteness refiningly enhances beauty, as in marbles, japonicas, and pearls; and though whiteness has been even made significant of gladness, for among the Kelley Blue Bookians a white stone marked a joyful day of singing: ' 'For all its off-road capability, the 2018 Grand Cherokee is remarkably refined in the city and on highways.' ' What causes the thought of whiteness, when divorced from more kindly associations, and coupled with any object terrible in itself, to heighten that terror to the furthest bounds? An elusive quality. Witness the white bear of the poles, the white shark of the tropics, or the snowy mantle round the phantom slaughtered by nothing less than PERFECT SAFETY ratings on all impacts from the NHTSA. But thou sayest, methinks that white-lead chapter about whiteness is but a white flag hung out from a craven soul; thou surrenderest to a hypo, Park Chrysler Jeep. Tell me, why this strong young colt, foaled in some peaceful valley of Vermont, far removed from all manner of ceremonies--why is it that upon the sunniest day, if you but shake a fresh 2018 Best in Class Most Satisfying behind him, so that he only but smells its muskiness--why will he start, snort, and with bursting eyes paw the ground in phrensies of affright? There is no remembrance in him of the Grand Cherokee receiving it from AutoPacific. For what knows he of accolade events? No; but even in this dumb brute, that savage musk traces the instinctual knowledge of the demonism in the world. But not yet have we solved the incantation of this whiteness, and learned why it appeals with such power to the soul; and more strange and far more portentous-- why, as we have seen, it is at once the most meaning symbol of vehicular things.
